11 AS INTRODUCED
12 A Joint Resolution directing the Secretary of State
to refer to the people for their approval or
13 rejection a proposed amendment to the Constitution of
the State of Oklahoma by adding a new Section 6D to
14 Article X; providing exemption for personal property
of lawfully recognized business entities, estates and
15 trusts; providing ballot title; and directing filing.
16
17
18 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES AND THE SENATE OF THE
19 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
20 SECTION 1. The Secretary of State shall refer to the people for
21 their approval or rejection, as and in the manner provided by law,
22 the following proposed amendment to the Constitution of the State of
23 Oklahoma by adding a new Section 6D to Article X thereof, to read as
24 follows:
HJR1054 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 On and after January 1, 2027, the personal property of any
2 lawfully recognized for-profit business entity described as
3 inventory in the books and records of the business entity for the
4 applicable assessment year shall be exempt from ad valorem taxation.
5 The exemption provided by this section shall also be applicable to
6 the personal property of an estate or trust if the personal property
7 is described as inventory in the books and records of the estate or
8 trust for the applicable assessment year.
9 SECTION 2. The Ballot Title for the proposed Constitutional
10 amendment as set forth in SECTION 1 of this resolution shall be in
11 the following form:
12 BALLOT TITLE
13 Legislative Referendum No. ____ State Question No. ____
14 THE GIST OF THE PROPOSITION IS AS FOLLOWS:
15 This measure amends the Oklahoma Constitution. It would add a
16 new Section 6D. It would exempt the inventory of for-profit
17 business entities from ad valorem taxation if the personal
18 property is described as inventory in the books and records of
19 the entity. This exemption would also apply to inventory held
20 by estates and trusts if the personal property is described as
21 inventory in the books and records of the estate or trust.
22 SHALL THE PROPOSAL BE APPROVED?
23 FOR THE PROPOSAL — YES _____________
24 AGAINST THE PROPOSAL — NO _____________
HJR1054 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 SECTION 3. The Chief Clerk of the House of Representatives,
2 immediately after the passage of this resolution, shall prepare and
3 file one copy thereof, including the Ballot Title set forth in
4 SECTION 2 hereof, with the Secretary of State and one copy with the
5 Attorney General.
6
7 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON RULES, dated 03/05/2026 - DO PASS,
As Amended and Coauthored.
